Skip to main content Main menu Home About Issues & Policies Events Membership Research & Resources News Act Now Sponsorship Secondary menu Directory Jobs Log in Join SEIA Español SEIA Search Follow Us Facebook Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Google+ Pinterest Blog You are here Home Thursday, April 7, 2016 America’s Cities are ‘Shining’ Says New Report A new report unveiled Wednesday shows that America’s cities are taking solar seriously. The report, Shining Cities 2016: How Smart Local Policies Are Expanding Solar Power in America, ranks cities by total solar photovoltaic (PV) capacity installed and PV capacity per capita at the end of 2015, and provides policy recommendations for the federal, state and local governments that can spur solar deployments. Thursday, March 31, 2016 Demand For Utility-Scale Solar Still Dominating While more Americans than ever are installing solar on their homes and businesses, utility-scale projects are dominating the solar revolution and generating more clean, reliable and cost-effective electricity. Wednesday, March 30, 2016 #StorageIsHere: Like Solar, Storage Has Only Started To Hit Its Stride Like the panels that harness the sun’s rays, the batteries that store its energy can support the reliability of solar electricity. Efficient and affordable energy storage strengthens solar’s capacity to power homes from dusk to dawn, and may be the keystone needed for its proliferation. Wednesday, March 30, 2016 Industry Speaks Up For Solar In Massachusetts The solar industry went to the Massachusetts State House in Boston yesterday to deliver more than 5,000 petitions and letters to Democratic House Speaker Bob DeLeo, demanding lawmakers to act swiftly and decisively on keeping solar working in the state. Wednesday, March 23, 2016 #DoTheMath: How Rooftop Solar Will Save Us Billions The obvious cost savings of the tremendous rise in solar, particularly the proliferation of rooftop solar panels, is that it puts system owners in control of their energy needs and wrangles in their energy bills. Alone, the economic incentive for consumer-sited solar is strong, but what may be less evident is the impact solar adoption has for us all. Thursday, March 17, 2016 Let's SPARC More Communities To Go Solar The Solar Powering America by Recognizing Communities (SPARC) program has made significant progress toward its objectives of establishing a national designation for leading solar communities and empowering communities to become solar leaders through no-cost, customized technical assistance. Communities interested in joining SPARC can sign up! Tuesday, March 15, 2016 #solar4all: Guide Provides Roadmap For More Low-Income Communities To Go Solar A New Low-Income Solar Policy Guide outlines policies and program models that open access to solar power and solar jobs for all Americans, and identifies how these models can be replicated in more low-income communities. Thursday, March 10, 2016 Solar Is Helping Farmers Grow Sustainably Whitmore Farm turned to solar energy to help mitigate its operating costs and impact on the environment. It's paying off, and its owner suggests other farmers do the same. Wednesday, March 9, 2016 Solar Market Will Double This Year In just the next two years alone, the amount of solar capacity that is projected to be installed in the U.S. is roughly the same amount that has been installed ever since the beginning of time to now. Monday, March 7, 2016 Faith-Based Community Embraces Solar For Reverend Dr. Julie Josund, caring for the health of our planet goes hand-in-hand with the Christian faith. Josund, a pastor at Edmonds Lutheran Church in Washington State, has long envisioned a church that exemplifies her belief. Recently, her vision turned to reality. Pages 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 … next › last » Subscribe to Sign up for the latest alerts Get emails from SEIA and be the first to know about solar news and issues in your state. Or, sign up for our press list. About the Blog The Solar Energy Industries Association Solar Blog seeks to shine light on America's solar industry. Written by SEIA's senior staff and board members, the blog will keep readers up-to-date on the policy, research and campaigns happening in the industry. See How Much Solar Can Save You Bloggers Katherine Gensler Nat Kreamer Philip Haddix Rhone Resch Tom Kimbis Christopher Mansour Sean Gallagher Dan Whitten Justin Baca Comms Team Sara Birmingham Andrew Savage Tony Clifford Mike Healy Rhone Resch and Tom Kiernan Antuan Scott Arno Harris Troy Van Beek Sean Gallagher & Susan Williams Sloan Guest Blogger Upcoming Events Webinar The New Massachusetts Solar Net Metering Law: Key Provisions & How We Succeeded April 15, 2016 - 1:00pm EDT Political Event Western States Federal Lobby Day April 21, 2016 (All day) On Twitter Curious about the new #MA #solar net metering law? Then tomorrow's #webinar is one you can't afford to miss. t.co/kbV3MfpGHs reply retweet favorite Wind and #Solar Projects Change the West Texas Landscape By Providing New, Well-Paying Jobs t.co/QMqanBkJQS via @nbcdfw reply retweet favorite TODAY 3 EST: Join @SEIA's Mike Mendelsohn & @RockyMtnInst's Herve Touati for a corporate #renewables #webinar t.co/qLPaLmJ6Pk reply retweet favorite More Californians now work in “Advanced #Energy” jobs like #solar than in farming or Hollywood t.co/w0rm9aREV9 via @grist reply retweet favorite #Solar now accounts for nearly 3/4 of renewable generation employment in #RhodeIsland #SolarIsNow t.co/GiCAz9TqRA reply retweet favorite On seia.org About Events Issues & Policies Research News Act Now Membership Help Anti-Trust Contact Copyright Policy Credits Jobs Privacy Policy Terms of Service Solar Energy Industries Association 202-682-0556 | 600 14th Street, NW, Suite 400, Washington, DC 20005               Follow Us Facebook Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Google+ Pinterest
